Message from the ESU Drawing Committee 

Those who have lost or damaged their set squares while using must purchase and hand over *sets squares of the same brand* at the end of the semester. 

If anyone have lost or damaged their *tool boxes or tools* while using, please inform us. 

*All drawing equipment must be handed over at the end of the semester.*

Please use your drawing tools with care. The tools are really expensive and fines will have to be paid for any damages.

11/23/22, 11:04â€¯PM - Ravindu Dinelka: ğŸ›‘ğŸ›‘ğŸ›‘
Dear Executive committee,

Students Union is something big and has very serious issues to address. Everyone should follow the right steps to solve issues, and for all little little issues and problems don't use the names of ESU or ask President or Secretary to interfere and solve them. If Union is involved in all these little things the prestige of Union will be decreased. So try to solve everything in lower boundaries or contact all the possible people you can get the solution. And let the union takes care of very serious issues,  problems and developments. 

Like if there are any issues in a hostel, the hostel committee should take action. Students have to force them to take action. Don't inform ESU to take action. And if you want ESU to take any action inform us of the whole details transparently. Then we can decide whether to take action or not. 

If there are any issues try to approach them in these stages, 
1. Individual Appeal  
2. Students Appeal  
3. Batch representative ( For Faculty issues only) 4. ESU representative ( For Faculty issues only)
5. Specific Committee President/ Secretary 

 *Then only approach the Union President/ Secretary.* 

Please consider these things in the future and behave responsibly.

Thank you.

*Environmental pollution and Control project topic selection.*

Guys please update this list about the topics you select for the project to avoid  submission of same topic. 

1. AX1 - Proper Medical waste  disposal in Kilinochi general hospital

2. AX2 - Assessment of water quality in water resource in Jaffna Area.

3.AY3-Municipal solid waste management

04.CY1 - To ascertain the quality of water sources in a galewela area

05. AY4- Comparative study of color removal from drinking water using cheap/waste materials

06-Dx4 wastage management in garments in kilinochi permisses and surrounding areas

07-Dx2- complete waste assessment and management system in University of jaffna Kilinochchi premises

08- DX1 - Ocean pollution at coastline areas

09- AY2 - water pollution in rivers and canels in anuradhapura area

10. BX1- Prevention of environmental pollution  caused by pesticides used in agriculture

11- BX4-waste water treatment in kilinochi

12-CY3 - Soil erosion in nearby waterbodies

13-CY4-Water assessment and CKD analysis of anuradhapura region

14. Environmental pollution due to Industries in jaffna

15- BY2 -  Waste management and recycling of them in MAS and KIST

16.Cx4-To reduce the plastic wastages in university area.

17- DY4 - Analysis of medical waste disposing techniques in Anuradhapura general hospital.

18.DY3 Soil erosion of beach side from wennappuwa to chilaw

19. Dx3-Marine pollution due to solid waste

20-AY1-Analsis of coral reef  and Mangrove ecosystem destruction happens around  southern costal area

21. BY4 - Management of sewage instead of directly discharging it into railway tracks.

22.AX4-Dambulla Compost Plant

23- Cx3 - Waste management in faculty of engineering University of Jaffna

24- BY3-water problems faced by students in university

25.DY2- Medical waste and waste water management in Vavuniya general hospital.

26. BY1 - Solid waste management under the heavy metals.

27. Dy1 - Deforestation all over the country

28. CY2 - Garbage dump disposal around Anuradhapura area

29. AX3 - Water supply and management system in Anuradhapura religious places

12/3/22, 9:17â€¯PM - Imesh Uoj: let it stay

 Don't ask someone who doesn't go home even for a vacation that comes after a while!

 If someone says that they are thinking of being alone for the rest of their lives without love, don't ask them why!

 If you see the friend who told everyone to go to work drinking coffee alone in a coffee shop, why is he alone?  Don't ask!

 Don't ask someone who is addicted to books, "Dude, try an ilm like that"!
 If someone tells you his story, don't make decisions based on that story!  Just listen!

 For someone who is depressed because of a girl or a boy,

 "Look, what are these problems when you look at them?" Don't tell me!

 Don't say "Hena Lobaine Bang" to a friend who hasn't bought new clothes in years!

 Don't laugh if you see a BMW on the wallpaper of someone who earns 30,000!

 After about two years, a call came from a best friend.
  It's been a long time and now you've got it right.  Don't ask that you are so big!

 In short, never ask anyone anything other than what they say!

 People can say words

 Only things!  To free things that cannot be put into words, every person has his own way!

 Let those people be with them!

 Don't question people's habits!  Don't make decisions about people based on what you know!  People have reasons for saying and not saying things!
  "Everyone has a reason for everything!"

 Be a free man without question!  Morning and evening we see this, one life at a time

 People who bet with the seasons!

 So

 "Let the people be at a loss"

February 20th E22 will be starting their orientation. As decided both E21 and E22 are subjected to stay in the hostel until the E21 end exam finishes. ‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€ €‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹ Introducing Past Master: The Ultimate Study App for Advanced Level School Students

We are excited to present Past Master, the ultimate study app designed specifically for Sinhala, Tamil and English medium advanced level school students. With its comprehensive features and user-friendly interface, Past Master aims to revolutionize the way students prepare for their exams by providing access to past papers year-wise and unit-wise. We would like to take this opportunity to share the app's exciting features and benefits, encouraging its adoption within your educational community.

Key Features of Past Master:

1.MCQ Challenge Mode: Past Master offers an engaging MCQ challenge mode that allows students to tackle past papers year-wise and unit-wise. Students can select specific years and units to focus on, enabling them to tailor their practice sessions according to their individual needs and areas of improvement.

2.Performance Analysis: Past Master provides detailed performance analysis for each MCQ challenge attempted. Students can review their performance on a year-wise and unit-wise basis, gaining insights into their strengths and weaknesses in specific subjects and topics. This analysis empowers students to 

3.Comparative Analysis: The app includes a comparative analysis feature that allows students to benchmark their performance against their district-wise peers or island-wise students. This feature not only fosters healthy competition but also provides students with a sense of their relative strengths in comparison to their peers.

4.Vast Repository of Past Papers: Past Master boasts a vast collection of past papers, conveniently organized year-wise and unit-wise. This extensive database ensures that students have access to a wide range of practice material, allowing them to thoroughly prepare for their exams and gain confidence in each subject.

5.User-Friendly Interface: The app is designed with a user-friendly interface, making it intuitive and easy to navigate. Students can effortlessly select specific years, units, and subjects to access the corresponding past papers and MCQ challenges. The interface promotes a seamless and enjoyable study experience.

6.User Contributions: Past Master encourages active participation from users by allowing them to contribute their own past papers to the app. This collaborative approach ensures that the app remains updated with the latest papers, offering a dynamic and ever-growing collection for students. Users can contribute their past papers, thereby fostering a sense of community and shared knowledge.

7.Completely Free and Ad-Free: We are delighted to inform you that Past Master is a completely free app with no hidden charges or in-app purchases. We believe that every student should have access to quality education resources without any financial burden. Moreover, the app is ad-free, ensuring a distraction-free study environment for students.

Subject: Explanation for Not Meeting 80% Attendance Requirement

Dear [Professor's Name],

I hope this letter finds you in good health and high spirits. I am writing to address my current attendance record in your lectures and to provide an explanation for falling short of the 80% attendance requirement.

First and foremost, I would like to express my sincere apologies for not meeting the attendance expectation. I understand the importance of attending lectures regularly, and I regret that my attendance has been below the desired level. However, I would like to outline the circumstances that have contributed to this situation.

Health Issues: Unfortunately, during the semester, I have been dealing with a persistent health issue that has hindered my ability to attend lectures consistently. Despite my best efforts to manage my health, there were days when attending class was physically challenging, and I needed to prioritize my recovery.

Family Emergency: A few weeks ago, my family faced an unexpected emergency that required my immediate attention and support. I had to be present and provide assistance during this difficult time, which resulted in me missing several lectures.

Personal Obligations: I am also actively involved in extracurricular activities and community service, which sometimes clash with my lecture schedule. These commitments are essential to my personal growth and contribute to my overall development, but they occasionally result in conflicts that prevent me from attending lectures.

Prioritizing Coursework: As a conscientious student, I have consistently dedicated significant time outside of class to study the course material thoroughly. Although attending lectures is undeniably valuable, I have ensured that I remain up to date with the curriculum by seeking alternative resources and engaging with fellow students to fill in any knowledge gaps.

I genuinely value the education I am receiving at [University Name] and recognize the significance of attending lectures to maximize my learning experience. I understand that regular attendance fosters an active and participatory classroom environment, and I assure you that I am committed to improving my attendance moving forward.

In light of the aforementioned circumstances, I kindly request your understanding and leniency regarding my attendance record. I would be grateful for any assistance or guidance you can provide to help me catch up on missed material and to ensure that I am on track with the course requirements.

Thank you for your attention and understanding. I appreciate your commitment to delivering quality education and for considering my situation. If there is any further information or documentation you require, please do not hesitate to contact me. I look forward to discussing this matter with you and finding a suitable solution.

Yours sincerely,

[Your Name]

9/13/23, 9:45â€¯PM - Didula (à¶´à·œà¶§à·š) Aiya E21 UOJ: Calling for Volunteer Undergraduates: Apeksha Hospital Energy Audit Initiative

Dear Enthusiastic Engineering Undergraduates,

The Electrical, Electronic, and Telecommunication Engineering Sectional Committee (EETESC) of IESL is embarking on an exciting journey to conduct a complimentary walkthrough energy audit at Apeksha Hospital, Maharagama.

Given the absence of essential electrical layout drawings at the hospital, we've taken the initiative to assemble a dedicated team of volunteer university undergraduates to tackle this challenge. This collaborative effort is estimated to span over a span of 2 months with the guidance of Chartered Electrical Engineers and Senior Lecturers of Engineering Faculties. The proper training will be provided. Volunteers who contribute sufficiently will receive letters of appreciation mentioning the trainings they have accomplished.

We extend a warm invitation to you to be a part of this dynamic group, contributing to the preparation of drawings and the collection of vital data.

_Google form Link: https://forms.gle/yYbHLfMTm9FEwDS97_

Submission Deadline: 9:00 PM, September 14th, 2023.

Warm Regards,
EETESCÂ ofÂ IESL

Hello everyone,

Civil & Environmental Engineering Society of University of Jaffna successfully published the second issue of the Nail magazine last week. And next issue of the magazine will be published in January 2024, If youâ€™re interested in contributing an article for the next issue of the magazine, you can write articles on any topic, preferably related to engineering. You can also submit your digital artwork and photographs with a context related to engineering. The editorial panel will choose quality works  for publication. 

Here are some guidelines for submitting your work:
*â€¢* Articles should be around 2500 (Min 2000) words and should be written in English 
*â€¢* Your artwork can be in any medium, but it should be created digitally. If you want to submit a non-digital drawing, send it as a scanned file or as a photograph
*â€¢* Photographs should be high resolution (at least 300 dpi) and in jpeg or png format
*â€¢* Please include a brief bio and a headshot with your photograph submission. 
*â€¢* All submitted works will be reviewed by the editorial panel
*â€¢* You can submit your work anytime before *15th of November 2023* and we will review your submission and get back to you as soon as possible. 

Previous issues and current issue of the Nail can be viewed here:
https://publication.jfn.ac.lk/nail/

Serving on the Executive Committee is a fantastic way to contribute to our vibrant IEEE community, shape the future of our branch, and develop valuable leadership skills. We are seeking passionate individuals with a commitment to excellence and a vision for driving our IEEE-SB-UoJ forward.

2/10/24, 10:04â€¯AM - Pramuda (à¶¸à¶§à·) Aiya E21 UOJ: Dear  Students,
                We are pleased to announce the availability of studentships to assist those facing financial challenges in pursuing their education. The deadline for application submission is March 4, 2024, at 11.59 pm. All enrolled students experiencing financial hardship are eligible to apply. Current recipients of financial support are also required to submit the application form to ensure the continuity of their assistance; failure to do so may result in a pause or termination of current support. The application process involves two steps: firstly, fill and certify the form with Grama Niladhari, and secondly, complete the online application, including uploading the signed form. For any clarifications or assistance, please contact me at mayooran@eng.jfn.ac.lk. We encourage all eligible students to take advantage of this opportunity for financial aid.


Application Process:

The application process involves two steps:

Application Form Submission:
Fill out the application form available at http://tinyurl.com/4wauatmh or simply scan the QR Code given below.
Certify all information by visiting your local Grama Niladhari. 
Online Application Submission:
Fill out the online application http://tinyurl.com/3w25fnt8 or simply scan the QR Code given below and upload the signed form as part of the process.

Submit the form in person at the AR Office (which is located on the ground floor of the admin building).

Express Your Interest in Building the Future of Entrepreneurship at University of Jaffna

Are you passionate about innovation, leadership, and creating your own path in the business world? Join us in laying the foundation for the Entrepreneurship Club at the University of Jaffna, Faculty of Engineering!

Why Join the Entrepreneurship Club?

* Networking Opportunities: Connect with like-minded individuals, mentors, and industry professionals who share your passion for entrepreneurship.
* Skill Development: Sharpen your entrepreneurial skills through workshops, seminars, and hands-on activities designed to foster creativity, problem-solving, and strategic thinking.
* Collaborative Projects: Work on real-world projects, startup ventures, and competitions that challenge you to apply your knowledge and make a tangible impact.
* Resource Access: Gain access to resources, funding opportunities, and support networks to help turn your ideas into successful ventures.
* Community Engagement: Engage with the local community through outreach initiatives, partnerships, and events that promote entrepreneurship and innovation.

Express Your Interest Today!

If you're ready to embark on an exciting journey of entrepreneurship and make a difference in the world, we want to hear from you! Express your interest by filling out the form below:

https://forms.gle/xmw9XQqFw1gTiQHfA

Location: MECHANICAL ENGINEERING LECTUER HALL

For more information, contact us at +94776950774 (Kajenthiran - Manager / Incubation Center).

Don't miss this opportunity to be a part of something extraordinary! Join the Entrepreneurship Club and let's create a future filled with innovation, growth, and endless possibilities.

Together, let's build the future of entrepreneurship at University of Jaffna, Faculty of Engineering!
